Day 7 Reflection

Day 7 served as my first major milestone in my cybersecurity journey.

Scoring 95/100 on a 100-question ISC2 CC-style assessment showed that the concepts covered during the first week have been well understood and retained.

The Linux Security & System Investigation project helped transform theoretical knowledge into practical experience. I gained confidence working with Linux commands, file permissions, processes, and system logs.

Key lessons learned:

* Security is built on strong fundamentals.
* Linux skills are essential for cybersecurity professionals.
* Logs provide critical visibility into system activity.
* Proper permissions reduce security risks.
* Continuous practice is necessary for certification success.

Next week I will begin Networking Fundamentals, covering TCP/IP, OSI Model, Ports, Protocols, and Network Security.
